sections.name: Referral form for follow-up allied health services under Medicare for People of Aboriginal or Torres Strait Islander descent

fields.label: Note: GPs can use this form issued by the Department of Health or one that contains all of the  components of this form.

groups.label: Eligible patients may access Medicare rebates for up to 5 allied health services (in total) in a calendar year. Indicate the number of  services required by writing the number in the ‘No. of services’ column next to the relevant AHP.
The AHP must provide a written report to the patient’s GP after the first and last service, and more often if clinically necessary.

sections.name: To be completed by referring GP

groups.label: Allied health professionals should retain this referral form for record keeping and Department of Human Services (Medicare) audit purposes.
Medicare rebates and Private Health Insurance benefits cannot both be claimed for these services. Patients should be advised that they must choose whether to access one or the other.
This form may be downloaded from the Department of Health website at www.health.gov.au/mbsprimarycareitems.
THIS FORM DOES NOT HAVE TO ACCOMPANY MEDICARE CLAIMS
